The integration test with two backends wired together in-memory is the most valuable -- it proves the full q:* round-trip through the proxy layer without needing the actual cloud relay, which can be tested separately.

I now have a complete understanding of the system. Here is the design.

---

## Approach Name: **Relay Peer Registry**

## Philosophy

The relay already solves the hard problem -- NAT traversal via a cloud intermediary. Desktop Mesh is not peer-to-peer; it is *peer-to-relay-to-peer*. The data structure that's missing is a **peer registry**: each desktop registers itself as both a *server* (exposing its own data) AND a *client* (discovering and subscribing to other desktops). Get the registry right and the rest is just plumbing existing q:* frames through a second hop.

## Current Architecture Summary

The system today has exactly one role per desktop: **server**. The relay.service.ts connects outbound to the cloud relay, registers as a server, and creates virtual `WsSendable` connections for remote web clients. Those clients speak the q:* protocol against the local query-engine, which reads the local SQLite DB. The data flow is strictly one-directional: *remote client reads local desktop's data*.

The key insight is that the q:* protocol is already transport-agnostic -- it works over local WS, over relay-tunneled virtual connections, and over direct WS connections. The protocol doesn't care *where* the data comes from. What we need is for Desktop A to act as a *client* of Desktop B through the relay, speaking the same q:* frames but prefixed with a peer identifier.

## Data Structures First

The core data structure is the **PeerDescriptor** -- what does the local desktop know about each peer in the mesh?

```typescript
// shared/types/mesh.ts
// The central data structure for the Desktop Mesh.

/** Identity of a peer desktop in the mesh. Immutable after registration. */
export interface PeerDescriptor {
  /** Relay-assigned server ID (8-char hex). Globally unique. */
  readonly serverId: string;
  /** Human-readable name (e.g., "Adam's MacBook Pro", "GPU Cluster 3"). */
  readonly serverName: string;
  /** Our device token for authenticating with this peer's relay tunnel. */
  readonly deviceToken: string;
  /** Relay URL this peer connects through. Usually the same for all peers. */
  readonly relayUrl: string;
}

/** Runtime state of a peer connection. Mutable. */
export interface PeerConnection {
  readonly peer: PeerDescriptor;
  status: "connecting" | "connected" | "disconnected" | "auth_failed";
  /** The relay-assigned clientId for our connection to this peer. */
  relayClientId: string | null;
  /** Active q:* subscriptions we hold against this peer, keyed by local sub ID. */
  subscriptions: Map<string, PeerSubscription>;
  /** Monotonic reconnect attempt counter. Resets on successful connect. */
  reconnectAttempt: number;
}

/** A subscription we hold against a remote peer's query engine. */
interface PeerSubscription {
  id: string;
  resource: QueryResource;
  params?: Record<string, unknown>;
  onSnapshot: (data: unknown) => void;
  onDelta?: (upserted?: unknown[], removed?: string[], cursor?: number) => void;
}

/** Wire format additions for mesh frames through the relay. */

// Peer discovery: relay tells us about other servers on the same account.
// This is a NEW relay frame type.
export interface MeshPeerAnnounce {
  type: "mesh:peer_announce";
  peers: Array<{
    serverId: string;
    serverName: string;
    online: boolean;
  }>;
}

// Mesh connection request: desktop asks relay to connect it to another server.
// Relay bridges the two tunnel WebSockets.
export interface MeshConnectRequest {
  type: "mesh:connect";
  targetServerId: string;
  deviceToken: string;
}

export interface MeshConnectResponse {
  type: "mesh:connect_result";
  targetServerId: string;
  success: boolean;
  /** Relay-assigned virtual client ID for routing data frames. */
  clientId?: string;
  error?: string;
}

// Data frames between peers reuse the existing { type: "data", clientId, payload }
// envelope. The clientId identifies which peer connection the data belongs to.
// The payload is a q:* frame, identical to what web clients send.
```

## Critical Insight: The Relay Is the Router

The biggest architectural decision is: **do we open a second WebSocket per peer, or multiplex through the existing tunnel?**

Answer: **Multiplex through the existing tunnel.** Each desktop already has exactly one tunnel WebSocket to the relay. The relay already multiplexes multiple clients over that single tunnel using `clientId`. A peer desktop is just another "client" from the relay's perspective -- the relay assigns it a clientId and routes data frames bidirectionally.

This means the relay Durable Object needs one new capability: when Server A says `mesh:connect` to Server B, the relay creates a virtual client on Server B's tunnel and a virtual client on Server A's tunnel, then bridges data frames between them. Both servers see a new `client_connected` and can validate the device token. Both servers' query-engines handle q:* frames identically whether they come from a web browser or a peer desktop.

## Implementation Sketch

### 1. `backend/src/services/mesh.service.ts` -- Peer Mesh Manager

This is the new module. It manages outbound peer connections (Desktop A connecting to Desktop B's data through the relay).

```typescript
// backend/src/services/mesh.service.ts
// Desktop Mesh — manages connections to peer desktops through the relay.
//
// Data structure invariant: every entry in `peers` has exactly one matching
// clientId in the relay's clientToConn map (when connected). The peer's
// query engine sees us as just another relay client.

import { match } from "ts-pattern";
import type { PeerDescriptor, PeerConnection, PeerSubscription } from "../../../shared/types/mesh";
import type { QueryResource } from "../../../shared/types/query-protocol";
import { getSetting, saveSetting } from "./settings.service";

// ---- State ----

/** All known peers, keyed by serverId. Persisted in settings. */
const peers = new Map<string, PeerConnection>();

/** Maps relay-assigned clientId → peer serverId for incoming data routing. */
const clientToPeer = new Map<string, string>();

/** Callback to send frames through the relay tunnel. Set by relay.service. */
let sendToRelayFn: ((frame: Record<string, unknown>) => void) | null = null;

/** Callback to notify frontend of peer state changes. */
let onPeerStateChange: ((peers: PeerStatus[]) => void) | null = null;

// ---- Types ----

export interface PeerStatus {
  serverId: string;
  serverName: string;
  status: PeerConnection["status"];
  subscriptionCount: number;
}

// ---- Initialization ----

/**
 * Set the relay send function. Called once by relay.service when tunnel opens.
 * Decoupled so mesh.service has no import dependency on relay internals.
 */
export function setRelaySender(fn: (frame: Record<string, unknown>) => void): void {
  sendToRelayFn = fn;
}

/** Set the frontend notification callback. */
export function setOnPeerStateChange(fn: (peers: PeerStatus[]) => void): void {
  onPeerStateChange = fn;
}

/** Load persisted peer descriptors and attempt connections. */
export function initialize(): void {
  const stored = getSetting("mesh_peers") as PeerDescriptor[] | undefined;
  if (!stored || !Array.isArray(stored)) return;

  for (const desc of stored) {
    if (!peers.has(desc.serverId)) {
      peers.set(desc.serverId, {
        peer: desc,
        status: "disconnected",
        relayClientId: null,
        subscriptions: new Map(),
        reconnectAttempt: 0,
      });
    }
  }

  // Attempt connections for all known peers
  connectAll();
}

// ---- Public API ----

/** Add a peer and initiate connection. Persists to settings. */
export function addPeer(descriptor: PeerDescriptor): void {
  if (peers.has(descriptor.serverId)) return;

  peers.set(descriptor.serverId, {
    peer: descriptor,
    status: "disconnected",
    relayClientId: null,
    subscriptions: new Map(),
    reconnectAttempt: 0,
  });

  persistPeers();
  connectToPeer(descriptor.serverId);
}

/** Remove a peer, close connection, clean up subscriptions. */
export function removePeer(serverId: string): void {
  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn) return;

  // Clean up relay routing
  if (conn.relayClientId) {
    clientToPeer.delete(conn.relayClientId);
  }
  conn.subscriptions.clear();
  peers.delete(serverId);

  persistPeers();
  notifyFrontend();
}

/** Get status of all peers. */
export function getPeerStatuses(): PeerStatus[] {
  return [...peers.values()].map((c) => ({
    serverId: c.peer.serverId,
    serverName: c.peer.serverName,
    status: c.status,
    subscriptionCount: c.subscriptions.size,
  }));
}

/**
 * Subscribe to a resource on a remote peer. Returns unsubscribe function.
 * Identical API to the local query-protocol-client's subscribe().
 */
export function subscribeToPeer(
  serverId: string,
  resource: QueryResource,
  params: Record<string, unknown> | undefined,
  onSnapshot: (data: unknown) => void,
  onDelta?: (upserted?: unknown[], removed?: string[], cursor?: number) => void,
): () => void {
  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn) throw new Error(`Unknown peer: ${serverId}`);

  const subId = `mesh_${serverId}_${++subCounter}`;
  const sub: PeerSubscription = { id: subId, resource, params, onSnapshot, onDelta };
  conn.subscriptions.set(subId, sub);

  // If connected, send subscribe frame immediately
  if (conn.status === "connected" && conn.relayClientId) {
    sendToPeer(conn, {
      type: "q:subscribe",
      id: subId,
      resource,
      ...(params ? { params } : {}),
    });
  }

  return () => {
    conn.subscriptions.delete(subId);
    if (conn.status === "connected" && conn.relayClientId) {
      sendToPeer(conn, { type: "q:unsubscribe", id: subId });
    }
  };
}

let subCounter = 0;

// ---- Relay Frame Handlers ----
// Called by relay.service when it receives mesh-specific frames.

/** Handle mesh:connect_result from relay. */
export function handleConnectResult(
  targetServerId: string,
  success: boolean,
  clientId?: string,
  error?: string,
): void {
  const conn = peers.get(targetServerId);
  if (!conn) return;

  if (success && clientId) {
    conn.status = "connected";
    conn.relayClientId = clientId;
    conn.reconnectAttempt = 0;
    clientToPeer.set(clientId, targetServerId);

    // Re-subscribe all active subscriptions
    for (const sub of conn.subscriptions.values()) {
      sendToPeer(conn, {
        type: "q:subscribe",
        id: sub.id,
        resource: sub.resource,
        ...(sub.params ? { params: sub.params } : {}),
      });
    }
  } else {
    conn.status = error?.includes("auth") ? "auth_failed" : "disconnected";
    scheduleReconnect(targetServerId);
  }

  notifyFrontend();
}

/** Handle incoming data frame from a peer (routed by relay via clientId). */
export function handlePeerData(clientId: string, payload: string): void {
  const serverId = clientToPeer.get(clientId);
  if (!serverId) return;

  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn) return;

  let msg: Record<string, unknown>;
  try {
    msg = JSON.parse(payload);
  } catch {
    return;
  }

  const type = typeof msg.type === "string" ? msg.type : "";

  match(type)
    .with("q:snapshot", () => {
      const sub = conn.subscriptions.get(msg.id as string);
      sub?.onSnapshot(msg.data);
    })
    .with("q:delta", () => {
      const sub = conn.subscriptions.get(msg.id as string);
      sub?.onDelta?.(
        msg.upserted as unknown[] | undefined,
        msg.removed as string[] | undefined,
        msg.cursor as number | undefined,
      );
    })
    .with("q:response", () => {
      const sub = conn.subscriptions.get(msg.id as string);
      sub?.onSnapshot(msg.data);
    })
    .with("q:error", () => {
      console.warn(`[Mesh] Query error from peer ${serverId}:`, msg.message);
    })
    .with("q:invalidate", () => {
      // Re-subscribe to affected resources to get fresh data
      const resources = msg.resources as string[];
      for (const sub of conn.subscriptions.values()) {
        if (resources.includes(sub.resource)) {
          // Server-side push-first invalidation should handle this,
          // but if not, re-request
          sendToPeer(conn, {
            type: "q:request",
            id: sub.id,
            resource: sub.resource,
            ...(sub.params ? { params: sub.params } : {}),
          });
        }
      }
    })
    .with("ping", () => {
      sendToPeer(conn, { type: "pong" });
    })
    .otherwise(() => {
      // Ignore unknown frame types
    });
}

/** Handle peer disconnected notification from relay. */
export function handlePeerDisconnected(clientId: string): void {
  const serverId = clientToPeer.get(clientId);
  if (!serverId) return;

  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn) return;

  clientToPeer.delete(clientId);
  conn.relayClientId = null;
  conn.status = "disconnected";

  notifyFrontend();
  scheduleReconnect(serverId);
}

/** Called when the relay tunnel itself reconnects. Re-establish all peer connections. */
export function onTunnelReconnect(): void {
  for (const conn of peers.values()) {
    conn.status = "disconnected";
    conn.relayClientId = null;
  }
  connectAll();
}

/** Called when the relay tunnel disconnects. Mark all peers disconnected. */
export function onTunnelDisconnect(): void {
  for (const [clientId] of clientToPeer) {
    clientToPeer.delete(clientId);
  }
  for (const conn of peers.values()) {
    conn.status = "disconnected";
    conn.relayClientId = null;
  }
  notifyFrontend();
}

// ---- Internal ----

function connectAll(): void {
  if (!sendToRelayFn) return;
  for (const serverId of peers.keys()) {
    connectToPeer(serverId);
  }
}

function connectToPeer(serverId: string): void {
  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn || !sendToRelayFn) return;
  if (conn.status === "connecting" || conn.status === "connected") return;

  conn.status = "connecting";
  notifyFrontend();

  sendToRelayFn({
    type: "mesh:connect",
    targetServerId: serverId,
    deviceToken: conn.peer.deviceToken,
  });
}

function sendToPeer(conn: PeerConnection, frame: Record<string, unknown>): void {
  if (!sendToRelayFn || !conn.relayClientId) return;

  sendToRelayFn({
    type: "data",
    clientId: conn.relayClientId,
    payload: JSON.stringify(frame),
  });
}

const RECONNECT_BASE_MS = 2_000;
const RECONNECT_MAX_MS = 30_000;
const reconnectTimers = new Map<string, ReturnType<typeof setTimeout>>();

function scheduleReconnect(serverId: string): void {
  if (reconnectTimers.has(serverId)) return;
  const conn = peers.get(serverId);
  if (!conn) return;

  const delay = Math.min(
    RECONNECT_BASE_MS * 2 ** conn.reconnectAttempt,
    RECONNECT_MAX_MS,
  );
  conn.reconnectAttempt++;

  reconnectTimers.set(
    serverId,
    setTimeout(() => {
      reconnectTimers.delete(serverId);
      connectToPeer(serverId);
    }, delay),
  );
}

function persistPeers(): void {
  const descriptors = [...peers.values()].map((c) => c.peer);
  saveSetting("mesh_peers", descriptors);
}

function notifyFrontend(): void {
  onPeerStateChange?.(getPeerStatuses());
}
```

