### 3. Changes to `relay.service.ts` -- Wire Mesh Into Existing Tunnel

The changes are surgical. The relay tunnel already handles all frame types via `handleRelayFrame`. We add three new cases:

```typescript
// In handleRelayFrame, add to the match:
.with({ type: "mesh:connect_result" }, (f) => {
  handleConnectResult(f.targetServerId, f.success, f.clientId, f.error);
})
.with({ type: "mesh:peer_announce" }, (f) => {
  // Forward to mesh service for peer discovery
  handlePeerAnnounce(f.peers);
})
// The "data" case already exists but needs to check if clientId belongs to a peer:
// In the existing "data" handler, add a check:
.with({ type: "data" }, (f) => {
  // Check if this is peer mesh data (outbound subscription response)
  if (isPeerClientId(f.clientId)) {
    handlePeerData(f.clientId, f.payload);
    return;
  }

  // Existing local client handling...
  const connId = clientToConn.get(f.clientId);
